<br>
Place: Bastion of Thunder, south pad<br>
<br>
Problem:  Named up (Sandstorm), and Swavay, a Dragons of Northstar member decides that our group will be unable to kill named so he calls his guild to 'help'.  Now if you're not gonna help and just gonna have your guild take a named from an established group, be upfront and thank the group for bein slow and quit group and go join your guild.<br>
<br>
Vanston and the DoN show up, set up and in the kindness of their hearts clear the pops around the named for us.  The whole time im expecting DoN to help themselves to named, the rest of the group is thinkin the same, Swavay is sayin there is no way we could do it, the main tank is saying his wizard hydra is a few min away. So group is feelin hurried and concerned at possible theft of mob that the DoN wouldnt have known about had Swavay kept quiet. We have a rogue on standby to help, but DoN is clearin the room and Swavay keeps pointin out he might have to leave the group to help his guild.<br>
<br>
Now i'll be the first to agree that our group was a bit lethargic in attacking the named, and that we weren't 100% when we did pull him, but how crappy is it for someone in a group to call their guild, tell them a named is up and that the group they're in probably couldnt do it.  <br>
<br>
Our 65sk went down, then the pally and when oom and gettin aggro i headed for the pad, there on the other side was Dragons of Northstar all ready to pounce on the named.  Dunno what dropped, dont really care.  Just think if you're in a group your responsibility is to the ppl who let ya join with them and not to sell them out for your guild.<br>
<br>
When i mentioned it to Swavay, he said that if i knew Vanston then i'd know thats what to expect, well i don't know Vanston, and im thinkin thats not a bad thing.<br>
<br>
rant over<br>
